rows.content: One fun fact about the Roman Empire is that they had a sewer goddess. The Romans were known for their advanced engineering skills, including their sophisticated sewage systems. The Cloaca Maxima, one of the world's earliest sewage systems, is a testament to their engineering prowess. To ensure the proper functioning and maintenance of their sewage system, the Romans worshipped Cloacina, the goddess of the Cloaca Maxima. Cloacina was initially a protector of sexual purity and marital fidelity, but her role expanded to include the oversight of the sewer system, emphasizing the importance the Romans placed on sanitation and public health.
